<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-374-144  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 374 144.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  June 12 1989 v3 n24 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New Air Force group to centralize computer buys.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Air Force has formed a new division to consolidate thedevelopment, acquisition, and support of standard computersystems.andP;  The Computer Systems Division (CSD) will be headed by ageneral officer and is expected to make the Air Force's computeracquisition offices more visible.andP;  The new division will be partof the Air Force Communications Command.andP;  The reorganization isdesigned to streamline management and provide central, consistentpolicy and guidance.andP;  The CSD will perform a crucial role inlong-range planning for setting standards and keeping up withtechnology in computers and software.andP;  The two current computeracquisition units, the Air Force Standard Systems Center (SSC) andthe Air Force Computer Acquisition Center (AFCAC), will be underthe command of the CSD.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Air ForcePurchasing SystemsComputer SystemsReorganization.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>